      <h3 class="primary-color"><strong>Your  Available Resources</strong></h3><br>
      <p>After determining your insurance needs,  it is necessary to find out what resources you already have to meet this need.  Essentially, if you need $1,000,000 to provide for your beneficiaries and you  have more resources than that, then you do not need to buy any more life  insurance (death benefits). You only need to purchase if there is a shortfall.<br><br>
      Your available resources can be found  in 2 main sources.</p><br>
